            "title": "المعادلات التفاضلية الاعتيادية",
            "english_title": "Ordinary Differential Equations",
            "pages": [
                {
                    "page_number": 220,
                    "sections": [
                        {
                            "type": "section_header",
                            "title_arabic": "[5-5] بعض طرق حل المعادلات التفاضلية",
                            "title_english": "Some methods for solving differential equations"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "subsection_header",
                            "title_arabic": "المعادلات التي تنفصل متغيراتها",
                            "title_english": "Separation of Variables"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content_arabic": "في هذا النوع من المعادلات وكما يظهر من اسمها نستطيع ان نعزل كل الحدود التي تحتوي على X فقط مع dx في جانب والحدود التي تحتوي على Y فقط مع dy في الجانب الآخر فنحصل على:"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "equation",
                            "latex": "$$f(x)dx = g(y)dy \\\\dots (1)$$"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content_arabic": "ثم تكامل طرفي المعادلة (1) فيكون"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "equation",
                            "latex": "$$\\int g(y)dy = \\\\int f(x)dx + c$$"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "note",
                            "content_arabic": "حيث c ثابت اختياري (Arbitrary Constant)"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "example",
                            "id": 1,
                            "title_arabic": "مثال - 1",
                            "problem_arabic": "حل المعادلة $\\\\frac{dy}{dx} = 2x+5$",
                            "solution_arabic": [
                                {
                                    "type": "paragraph",
                                    "content_arabic": "الحل"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 2x+5 \\\\implies dy = (2x+5)dx$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\int dy = \\\\int (2x+5)dx \\\\implies y = x^2+5x+c$$"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "example",
                            "id": 2,
                            "title_arabic": "مثال - 2",
                            "problem_arabic": "حل المعادلة $\\\\frac{dy}{dx} = \\\\frac{x-1}{y}$",
                            "solution_arabic": [
                                {
                                    "type": "paragraph",
                                    "content_arabic": "الحل"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "content_arabic": "نجعل المعادلة بالصورة $g(y)dy = f(x)dx$ اي:",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$ydy = (x-1)dx$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "content_arabic": "بأخذ التكامل للطرفين:",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\int ydy = \\\\int (x-1)dx$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\frac{1}{2}y^2 = \\\\frac{1}{2}x^2-x+c$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$y^2 = x^2-2x+2c \\\\implies y=\\\\pm \\\\sqrt{x^2-2x+2c}$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$y=\\\\pm \\\\sqrt{x^2-2x+C_1}$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "note",
                                    "content_arabic": "(لكون C ثابت اختياري فإن 2C ثابت اختياري أيضاً اسميناه $C_1$)"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "page_number": 221,
                    "sections": [
                        {
                            "type": "example",
                            "id": 3,
                            "title_arabic": "مثال - 3",
                            "problem_arabic": "حل المعادلة التفاضلية $dy = \\\\sin x \\\\cos^2 y \\\\ dx$ حيث $y \\\\neq (2n+1)\\\\frac{\\\\pi}{2}, \\\\cos y \\\\neq 0$.",
                            "solution_arabic": [
                                {
                                    "type": "paragraph",
                                    "content_arabic": "الحل"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "content_arabic": "نجعل المعادلة بالشكل $g(y)dy = f(x)dx$",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\frac{1}{\\\\cos^2 y} dy = \\\\sin x \\\\ dx$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "content_arabic": "اي:",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\sec^2 ydy = \\\\sin x \\\\ dx$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "content_arabic": "باخذ التكامل",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\int \\\\sec^2 ydy = \\\\int \\\\sin x \\\\ dx$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "solution_final",
                                    "content_arabic": "حيث C ثابت اختياري",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\tan y = -\\\\cos x + C$$"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "example",
                            "id": 4,
                            "title_arabic": "مثال - 4",
                            "problem_arabic": "اوجد الحل العام للمعادلة التفاضلية $y' - x\\\\sqrt{y} = 0$ عندما $x=2, y=9$.",
                            "solution_arabic": [
                                {
                                    "type": "paragraph",
                                    "content_arabic": "الحل"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$y' - x\\\\sqrt{y} = 0 \\\\implies \\\\frac{dy}{dx} - x\\\\sqrt{y} = 0 \\\\implies \\\\frac{dy}{dx} = x\\\\sqrt{y}$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\frac{1}{\\\\sqrt{y}} dy = x \\\\ dx \\\\implies \\\\int y^{-\\\\frac{1}{2}}dy = \\\\int xdx$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$2\\\\sqrt{y} = \\\\frac{1}{2}x^2+C$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "content_arabic": "بالتعويض عن $x=2, y=9$ ينتج",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$2\\\\sqrt{9} = \\\\frac{1}{2}(2)^2+C \\\\implies 2(3) = \\\\frac{1}{2}(4)+C \\\\implies 6 = 2+C \\\\implies C = 4$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "paragraph",
                                    "content_arabic": "اذن الحل هو:"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "solution_final",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$2\\\\sqrt{y} = \\\\frac{1}{2}x^2 + 4 \\\\implies y=(\\\\frac{1}{4}x^2+2)^2$$"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "page_number": 222,
                    "sections": [
                        {
                            "type": "example",
                            "id": 5,
                            "title_arabic": "مثال - 5",
                            "problem_arabic": "حل المعادلة $\\\\frac{dy}{dx} = e^{2x+y}$ عندما $x=0, y=0$.",
                            "solution_arabic": [
                                {
                                    "type": "paragraph",
                                    "content_arabic": "الحل"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\frac{dy}{dx} = e^{2x}e^y \\\\implies e^{-y}dy = e^{2x}dx$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\int e^{-y}(-1)dy = \\\\frac{1}{2}\\\\int e^{2x}(2)dx$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$-e^{-y} = \\\\frac{1}{2}e^{2x}+C$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "content_arabic": "بالتعويض عن $x=0, y=0$ ينتج",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$-e^0 = \\\\frac{1}{2}e^0+C \\\\implies -1 = \\\\frac{1}{2}+C \\\\implies C = -\\\\frac{3}{2}$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "paragraph",
                                    "content_arabic": "اذن الحل هو:"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$-e^{-y} = \\\\frac{1}{2}e^{2x}-\\\\frac{3}{2} \\\\implies e^{-y} = \\\\frac{1}{2}(3-e^{2x})$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\frac{1}{e^y} = \\\\frac{3-e^{2x}}{2}$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$e^y = \\\\frac{2}{3-e^{2x}}$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "solution_final",
                                    "content_arabic": "وبأخذ ln للطرفين ينتج:",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$y = \\\\ln|\\\\frac{2}{3-e^{2x}}|$$"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "example",
                            "id": 6,
                            "title_arabic": "مثال - 6",
                            "problem_arabic": "جد الحل العام للمعادلة التفاضلية: $(x+1)\\\\frac{dy}{dx} = 2y$.",
                            "solution_arabic": [
                                {
                                    "type": "paragraph",
                                    "content_arabic": "الحل"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\frac{dy}{y} = 2\\\\frac{dx}{x+1} \\\\implies \\\\int \\\\frac{dy}{y} = 2\\\\int \\\\frac{dx}{x+1}$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\ln|y| = 2\\\\ln|x+1|+C$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\ln|y|-\\\\ln|(x+1)^2|=C$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\ln|\\\\frac{y}{(x+1)^2}| = C \\\\implies \\\\frac{y}{(x+1)^2} = e^C$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "note",
                                    "content_arabic": "حيث $e^C = C_1$ ثابت اختياري."
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "step",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$|y| = C_1(x+1)^2$$"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "solution_final",
                                    "equation_latex": "$$\\\\therefore y = \\\\pm C_1(x+1)^2$$"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "page_number": 223,
                    "sections": [
                        {
                            "type": "section_header",
                            "title_arabic": "تمارين",
                            "title_english": "Exercises"
                        },
